Package org.sopra.api.exercises.exercise5

Interface EnergyNetworkAnalyzer

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractEnergyNetworkAnalyzer
public interface EnergyNetworkAnalyzer

This interface represents an energy network analyzer which is used to calculate maximum loads for power lines, producers & consumers in an energy networks.

  • createFlowGraph(org.sopra.api.model.Graph<org.sopra.api.model.EnergyNode, org.sopra.api.model.PowerLine>, java.util.Optional<java.util.Map<org.sopra.api.model.producer.Producer, java.lang.Integer>>, java.util.Optional<java.util.Map<org.sopra.api.model.consumer.Consumer, java.lang.Integer>>) provides functionality to convert energy graphs to flow graphs
  • calculateMaxFlow() uses the converted energy graph as input for calculation of maximum loads.
  • The results of the calculation are provided in getConsumerLevels(), getProducerLevels(), and getPowerLineLevels()

  • Method Details

    • createFlowGraph

      FlowGraph<EnergyNode> createFlowGraph​(Graph<EnergyNode,​PowerLine> graph, java.util.Optional<java.util.Map<Producer,​java.lang.Integer>> producerCapacities, java.util.Optional<java.util.Map<Consumer,​java.lang.Integer>> consumerCapacities)

      Creates a flow graph on base of the given energy graph.

      The created flow graph contains all nodes of given energy graph, but also additionally contains the super source node provided in AbstractEnergyNetworkAnalyzer and the super sink node provided in AbstractEnergyNetworkAnalyzer.

      For each power line in given energy graph, two flow edges with opposed directions and equal capacities are created. The capacity of the flow edges is equal to the capacity of the power line.

      For energy nodes of type Producer additional edges going from super source to every producer node are created. If the Optional of the producerCapacities argument is empty, the capacity of edges from super source to each producer is equal to the provided energy level (Producer.getProvidedPower()) of the corresponding producer. Otherwise, the capacities correspond to the values of the producerCapacities argument.

      For energy nodes of type Consumer additional edges going from every consumer node to super sink are created. If the Optional of the consumerCapacities argument is empty, the capacity of edges from each consumer to super sink is equal to the required energy level (Consumer.getRequiredPower()) of the corresponding consumer. Otherwise, the capacities correspond to the values of the consumerCapacities argument.

      Parameters:
      graph - Energy graph which is to be converted to a flow graph.
      producerCapacities - If present, initializes capacities from super source to producer (key) with integer (value) of given Map.
      consumerCapacities - If present, initializes capacities from consumers (key) to super sink with integer (value) of given Map.
      Returns:
      Flow graph corresponding to the given energy graph.
